    {
      "sim_variable": "LETHALITY_SCALE",
      "value": 1.25,
      "canonical_source": "designs/provincial/mass_battle_integration_v30.md",
      "section": "§3.1 LETHALITY_SCALE restoration (Audit Issue 1, highest severity)",
      "quoted_text": "Damage formula applies LETHALITY_SCALE multiplier",
      "calibration": {
        "target_band_per_turn_casualty_pct": [
          14,
          16
        ],
        "test_config": "T3 mirror Line vs Line, P4 C4 D5 M6",
        "n_runs": 60,
        "observed_mean_pct": 14.48,
        "observed_median_pct": 16.45,
        "observed_stdev_pct": 9.77,
        "observed_battle_turns_mean": 1.9,
        "winners": {
          "A": 26,
          "B": 32,
          "draw": 2
        },
        "robustness_across_5_seed_batches_pct": [
          14.25,
          15.48,
          14.52,
          15.17,
          16.03
        ]
      },
      "notes": "Spec §3.1 stated initial value 0.10 with \"iterate within 0.05-0.20\" PROVISIONAL license. Calibrated value 1.25 is outside that range because PP-233 formula correction (continuous net_successes) raises baseline lethality from 3.96%/turn (discrete-bucket model at L=1.0) to 13.38%/turn (continuous at L=1.0). With the correct formula shape, LETHALITY_SCALE acts as fine-tune around ≈1.0 rather than gross compensation. See commit body for full diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "sim_variable": "PP-233 damage formula shape",
      "value": "net_successes * (1 + Power) - DR",
      "canonical_source": "params/mass_combat.md",
      "section": "Core Formula (PP-233)",
      "quoted_text": "Damage dealt | successes × (1 + Power)",
      "notes": "v17-v22 implemented as discrete DAMAGE_BY_DEGREE buckets {Overwhelming:1+p, Success:p, Partial:1, Failure:0}. PP-233 specifies continuous successes × (1+Power). Step 4.2 corrects implementation to match PP-233. DAMAGE_BY_DEGREE dict retained as narrative degree label for downstream logging only. DR retained as damage-reduction subtractor: PP-233 originally folded DR into H (Health per Size); v22 HP model uses Size × BLOCK_SIZE and drops H entirely, leaving DR-as-reduction as the only surviving DR effect."
    },
    {
      "sim_variable": "BLOCK_SIZE",
      "value": 100,
      "canonical_source": "designs/provincial/mass_battle_v30.md",
      "section": "§A.3 Troop count",
      "quoted_text": "1 Size = block_size soldiers",
      "notes": "HP = TroopCount = Size × BLOCK_SIZE. Company scale: Size 4 unit = 400 HP. Pre-existing constant; ledgered in Step 4.2 because LETHALITY_SCALE calibration depends on the HP scale this constant produces."
    },
